FAIL_TO_PASS: when subcommand executable fails with other error and exitOverride then return in custom wrapper
when digit option defined and option-argument is -1x then negative not consumed
when specify unknown option with simple program then error
when specify just custom short flag then display version
when missing command-argument then shows help
when specify unknown option with subcommand and action handler then error
when digit option defined and command-argument is -1e+3 then negative not consumed
when program has subcommands and specify only unknown option then display help
when digit option defined and option-argument is -.1 then negative not consumed
when option-argument for short optional is -1e-3.0 then consumed=false
when digit option defined and command-argument is -1.2e+3 then negative not consumed
when command-argument is --1 then consumed=false
when option-argument for short optional is -x-1 then consumed=false
CommanderError
when unknown command then error
when option-argument for short optional... is --1 then consumed=false
when specify option without required value then throw CommanderError
when has conflicting option then throw CommanderError
when program has required option not specified and subcommand --help then help
when command has exitOverride and executable subcommand fails then program exit code is subcommand exit code
